# Rival / CortexOne Function Contract

- Runtime: Python 3.13
- Entry point: `cortexone_handler(event, context)` returning `{"statusCode": int, "body": ...}`
- `event` is the inner request object (the HTTP body is `{"event": {...}}`)
- Validate and default every field read from `event`
- Map client errors to 400, unexpected failures to 500
- Never hardcode or log API keys; read BYOK secrets from `os.environ`
- Respect run limits: 512 MB RAM, 300 s timeout, ephemeral filesystem
- Cap unbounded input; set `stats.truncated = true` when input is clipped
- Do not rely on persistence across runs; use external stores for state
- Keep paid tool pricing at or below $0.25 per run
- Publish path: paste code + `requirements.txt` into Studio Tool Editor, add Environment Secrets, recreate test cases, then publish a new immutable version
